'''Karoly D'ulin''' was a member of the mysterious militaristic order of female warriors known as the [[Mistryl Shadow Guard]]s.

==Biography==
In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], when a mission to transport the [[Hammertong/Legends|Hammertong]] prototype ended in a [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] ambush, Karoly found herself on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], and she was in the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Mos Eisley Cantina]] with her friend and comrade [[Shada D'ukal]] when [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] first met [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]].

[[File:Tonnika1.jpg|thumb|left|180px|Karoly (left) in [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina]].]]

As part of their attempt to hire a freighter to transport a stolen Hammertong module, the two Mistryl were masquerading as the [[Tonnika sisters/Legends|Tonnika sisters]]: Karoly was disguised as [[Senni Tonnika/Legends|Senni Tonnika]] while Shada posed as [[Brea Tonnika/Legends|Brea Tonnika]]. Their choice of disguise got them briefly arrested by [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] [[Parq]] before being freed by [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] agent [[Riij Winward]]&mdash;although a subsequent disagreement on who should get the Hammertong information saw the Mistryl stealing his freighter to transport the [[Superlaser/Legends|superlaser]] component, while he made off with their astromech, [[D4]], and a technical readout of the weapon.

During the Hammertong mission, Shada had regarded Karoly as keen but somewhat inexperienced; by [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], however, Karoly had become a veteran warrior, and she was dispatched by the [[Eleven Elders of the People|Eleven Elders of Emberlene]] to "recover" Shada on [[Borcorash]] as the Mistryl made steps to break their ties with [[Mazzic]]. Shada escaped, and Karoly's pursuit brought her to [[Bastion/Legends|Bastion]], where she allied herself with [[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Grodin Tierce]] against her old enemy [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Zothip]] of the [[Cavrilhu Pirates]].

Subsequently, Karoly agreed to bring [[Paloma D'asima]] to [[Yaga Minor/Legends|Yaga Minor]], to discuss an alliance between the Mistryl and the [[Imperial Remnant]]; however, when the schemes of [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Vilim Disra]] were exposed, and the false [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] was revealed as the actor [[Flim (Human)|Flim]], Karoly returned to [[Emberlene]] with her leader.

Karoly was probably related to [[Team Prime]] [[Manda D'ulin]], gunned down in the ambush at the Hammertong base, and also to an earlier Mistryl, [[Naradan D'ulin]].

==Behind the scenes==
[[Angela Staines]] portrayed Karoly D'ulin, disguised as [[Senni Tonnika/Legends|Senni Tonnika]], in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="StarWars.com Message Boards">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=152583&start=1545#16926420|thread=Holocron continuity database questions|user=[[Leland Chee|Leland Y Chee]]|date=2007-09-26|time=5:34 PM}}</ref>

